{"title":"Micro. - Generalidades de las bacterias-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Infectología/Micro. - Generalidades de las bacterias-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Generalidades\\Nde las bacterias","guid":"b4BaKSja1uokf7vUNDsm8Q","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Forma y Agrupación:","guid":"Zny6OjScLuAMq8HgbqBYFw","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Formas Básicas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Esféricas (cocos).","guid":"HY94gFdk7UBsEmyHBduCWA","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• Cilíndricas (bacilos).","guid":"A9YWQk73b0BF_YEaC41Vew","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"• Espiraladas (espirilos, espiroquetas).","guid":"VFhomTE6VF9cg1_JfHQmHg","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"• Variaciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"• Bacilos fusiformes (e.g., Fusobacterium nucleatum).","guid":"W1e27XnC4AlMzR1TRtRoKg","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"• Bacilos curvos con flagelo (e.g., Vibrio cholerae).","guid":"LUNkxGqfpew07XIoEI4d8g","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"• Agrupación:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• Cocos:","guid":"RT2UWBXApwgrsfsOGddYdQ","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• Cadenas: Streptococcus pyogenes.","guid":"Ud_t-RlcpRkMOoqWOFyoNA","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"• Racimos: Staphylococcus aureus.","guid":"TfjT-hjmTHYm_QBLa4hMeg","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"9","text":"• Bacilos:","guid":"cEs5txMPbNJxY87SdCFP-Q","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• Cadenas, e.g., Lactobacillus acidophilus.","guid":"YgbcEjdhT-1_rqV0Nl9ErA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"1","text":"Tamaño:","guid":"PjYe_U7LyGtllb8ZLxhD4A","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"• General: 1-10 μm.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"• Extremos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Más pequeñas: Chlamydia (0.2 μm).","guid":"aJukTFwyBT0y02rKQ_NbOQ","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"• Más grandes: Epulopiscium fishelsoni (600 μm).","guid":"VfTlRn-giB0Kx8NjAzhKCg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"0","text":"Estructuras","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"Membrana Citoplasmática:","guid":"DCEFtBBvJ6ZbFbAbHAdkBg","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"• Ubicación: Delimita el citoplasma.","guid":"bgtk-UceVV1yFGDzKDVPUg","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"• Composición: Bicapa lipídica con proteínas hidrofóbicas.","guid":"YTMXLwIIz6xGF76edIN0CQ","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"21","text":"• Funciones: Transporte de nutrientes, producción de energía, barrera selectiva.","guid":"S7yuMWh--SsRM5P0WGhXcw","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"20","text":"Pared Celular:","guid":"Ic0cnlbJ0BcP5WBNIB03Ug","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"• Composición: Polímeros de azúcares (N-acetil-glucosamina y N-acetil-murámico).","guid":"Fk9gTllthDVZcM-hBSTb9A","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"• Función: Protección contra la presión osmótica.","guid":"FPVuRiR4F_cjBVtXWVXT8g","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"25","text":"• Tipos de bacterias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"• Gram-positivas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Pared gruesa (20-25 capas de peptidoglicano).","guid":"U9n9_ls_8IEI04KkL7_uiw","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• Ácidos teicoicos y lipoteicoicos.","guid":"fVXoF1icK7h7JjlBSEa2lw","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"• Sin membrana externa.","guid":"TOSQoHrHquh0apxHQzXFNA","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"28","text":"• Gram-negativas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"• Pared delgada (1-2 capas de peptidoglicano).","guid":"QIDbLhUR9f8FQ6f5brkEng","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"• Presencia de una membrana externa rica en lipopolisacáridos y fosfolípidos.","guid":"RuzjrB-54jE-vkqtT5Ghbw","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"33","text":"• Contienen proteínas como porinas que facilitan el paso de moléculas pequeñas.","guid":"ShV8ty7gyA1uhb-BTd6bcg","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"28","text":"• Micobacterias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Pared celular rica en ácidos micólicos y una capa lipídica externa.","guid":"eHQVDxKeuYdmnShzZn96CQ","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"• Resistencia alta a desinfectantes y antibióticos.","guid":"Wb0O5VixiWcOtMlbLZcM4w","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"• Características acido-alcohol resistentes (ej. Mycobacterium tuberculosis).","guid":"M_F56BeIS_9dVvtvMUdh_w","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"20","text":"Porinas:","guid":"bW2Q0SrKB_pasOicL2RlZA","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"• Función: Canales hidrofílicos formados por proteínas que permiten el paso pasivo de nutrientes y compuestos pequeños.","guid":"cCR3t1h9NLB5jhiWPQkIVw","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"20","text":"Estructura de las\\NBacterias Gram-negativas:","guid":"JTxXtUE9ChIZiS_4b1HUbQ","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"1. Membrana\\NCitoplasmática:","guid":"fH8hul3GKpMiAcTKMHCbog","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• Función: Transporte, producción de energía, barrera selectiva.","guid":"cB3SIAgO73o9MG_faJHnLw","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"• Composición: Bicapa lipídica con proteínas hidrofóbicas.","guid":"Gq2pASPNmFNPEWE4dGq35g","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"43","text":"2. Pared Celular:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• Delgada (1-2 capas de peptidoglicano).","guid":"dU52kn9YwDlht_2hZXLuSQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"43","text":"3. Membrana Externa:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"• Composición: Bicapa lipídica, rica en lipopolisacáridos (LPS) y lipoproteínas.","guid":"V9X06VtGFjcie_agKxrUgg","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"• Función: Barrera protectora adicional contra antibióticos y desinfectantes.","guid":"ST7LFSK6xCs-4I9JTEl18g","children":[]}]},{"id":"52","parent":"43","text":"4. Lipopolisacárido\\N(LPS):","guid":"HcluBCpdc0lG8YTVGkiPvg","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"• Composición:","guid":"KD05r0FfTq8WQQR7TXmRZQ","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"• Lípido A: Anclado en la membrana externa; actúa como endotoxina.","guid":"ApxYwS_KNHM8y2XScroq4Q","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"• Core-central: Región central del LPS, conectada al lípido A.","guid":"N9kj7Xn71bFbTBIRUobM7w","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"53","text":"• Antígeno O: Cadena repetitiva de azúcares; altamente antigénico, importante para la identificación de serotipos bacterianos.","guid":"CCOd3WjzSZ9KuStgfXIUbw","children":[]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"52","text":"• Función:","guid":"aEwJ2CxxKQFi5QK5QCH-wg","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"• Lípido A: Causa efectos tóxicos en el hospedero, contribuyendo a síntomas de shock séptico.","guid":"B7c_OQVg-VlrPNNEUPYKTg","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"• Antígeno O: Diferenciación de serotipos y especies bacterianas.","guid":"KBu9hSodYo4dP4BAUFj3NA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"60","parent":"43","text":"5. Periplasma:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"61","parent":"60","text":"• Ubicación: Espacio entre la membrana citoplasmática y la membrana externa.","guid":"a3yxPTOAhLsd0oiZbhkJ_g","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"60","text":"• Función: Contiene enzimas degradativas (β-lactamasas) y proteínas de transporte.","guid":"Y0q5Llqd7mtg0zTgGyPdHA","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"60","text":"• Contenido: Almacena hasta el 20% de las proteínas celulares.","guid":"VJnEHTwfRvFtqqoLcmMyIQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"20","text":"Endospora:","guid":"IS1FwlEN8YVkWQa1NoISfg","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"• Función: Supervivencia en condiciones adversas.","guid":"akAuCj-1NYsTxmf8L33CYg","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"• Resistencia: Desecación, temperaturas extremas, radiaciones, agentes químicos.","guid":"VXXclD94YwtJVRrXJ1XKjQ","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"• Ejemplos: Clostridium, Bacillus.","guid":"WNUIJFWPpW1fsnLBJs3cHg","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"64","text":"• Composición: Alta en calcio y ácido dipicolínico, pared gruesa.","guid":"bnXx5Aavcw0SViiYXsErmw","children":[]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"20","text":"Cápsula:","guid":"OxtHWFKRIQgyJQCeI7brpA","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"• Composición: Polisacáridos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"• Función:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"• Protección contra la fagocitosis.","guid":"Yiimth4SeL5V9C1-C_lPsg","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"71","text":"• Aumento de la virulencia (e.g., Streptococcus pneumoniae).","guid":"aWRedEtdFydn8Th5UG0BvA","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"71","text":"• Importancia Clínica: Factor de virulencia crítico en la patogénesis de algunas infecciones bacterianas.","guid":"Pxzkw0uGPaASpMWheoixJw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"75","parent":"20","text":"Capa de Secreción Viscosa\\N(Glicocálix):","guid":"Xg4ptAjgskZTMCHCfztvdw","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"• Composición: Polisacáridos menos adheridos que en la cápsula.","guid":"We6jyzeJKHg1vYH1GCTCyA","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"• Función:","guid":"J0C7-B6IjGc7PrUlEKUabA","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"• Protección contra desecación.","guid":"BlTw4xtTQQ5HPQaoEnX2lw","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"• Adhesión a superficies (e.g., formación de placa dental por Streptococcus mutans).","guid":"K8JotCJStsMufVqdGS_5hQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"75","text":"• Importancia: Facilita la colonización en superficies inertes y biológicas, contribuyendo a la formación de biopelículas","guid":"TRy-vQkuQzpIlF7pL0Vlcw","children":[]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"20","text":"Estructuras Relacionadas con la\\NMovilidad y Adherencia:","guid":"LsMmRWT4a2hnqkbdBLgLiw","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"Flagelos:","guid":"R_kD2nqPeSF4lMljSxOpFQ","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"• Función: Movilidad/motilidad bacteriana; considerado un factor de virulencia.","guid":"aeWjjyMv7Z9hEhwpKQKIUg","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"82","text":"• Tipos según ubicación:","guid":"fJeUEHa7WzxL_8RrVoY33A","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"• Monotrica: Un solo flagelo.","guid":"brYrP3O24cojizl5TMRU9A","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"• Lofotrica: Varios flagelos en un extremo.","guid":"LkSDtAG9RmBuqvqkNJl0lw","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"84","text":"• Anfitrica: Flagelos en ambos extremos.","guid":"HRCHbjXoAU1HD2suSNLwIg","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"84","text":"• Peritrica: Flagelos alrededor de toda la bacteria.","guid":"WDq4EHWMxcxiAumnJVd2zg","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"82","text":"• Importancia Taxonómica: El número y ubicación de los flagelos son característicos de la especie bacteriana.","guid":"frsJBiqXSJBUnNxBJfvE_g","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"82","text":"• Composición: Proteína flagelina.","guid":"SR_U-A_bkWc2oN9qMwV4hw","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"82","text":"• Función en la Infección: Permite a las bacterias penetrar en las mucosas y alcanzar células subyacentes.","guid":"Mwt_Bhey-5NcCADZIcGqRQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"81","text":"Fimbrias:","guid":"GstyKRq7SvcmaQZhMJQw_Q","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"• Función: Adhesión a superficies; no relacionadas con la movilidad.","guid":"C2ndXX-TOlJuhf85CAFxbg","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"• Composición: Proyecciones proteicas.","guid":"dk6VjjqFw6Reh6lKJJMZQg","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"92","text":"• Importancia: Facilitan la colonización de superficies biológicas e inertes.","guid":"PEMKBE0yo-5ZLI3ZWVORcg","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"92","text":"• Pilus: Tipo especializado de fimbria; involucrado en la conjugación bacteriana (transferencia de material genético).","guid":"AxqlOyA7-QgiJoGUW1VdTA","children":[]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"81","text":"Pili Cortos o Fimbrias:","guid":"Fci-1AQpazsArNQaFIPH2g","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"• Función: Adhesión a superficies, contribuyendo a la virulencia (factor de virulencia).","guid":"CNNn1gbuAiQ58msOFD1FMw","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"• Interacción: Adhesinas (pilina) con moléculas del hospedero.","guid":"BoE8dih4akccPrahfM_SBQ","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"97","text":"• Ejemplo: Neisseria gonorrhoeae (hemaglutinación, alta infectividad).","guid":"Yv4t7HrGX-shYutHH0E38A","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"81","text":"Filamento Axial:","guid":"HuS2MycV2ntFF_jXTaVp_w","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"• Función: Motilidad en un movimiento espiral.","guid":"fF-K13-Xha9FhfLDYYTMmQ","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"• Ubicación: Debajo de la membrana externa, a lo largo de la longitud de la bacteria.","guid":"cLfx8XBr9A55tY1ieYtZxw","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"101","text":"• Ejemplo: Treponema pallidum (causante de la sífilis).","guid":"d1n2MjOn-HANyJ77fdsyqA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"20","text":"Material Genético:","guid":"XCBityoHVZx6qwStPx6Qow","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"• Estructura del\\NCromosoma:","guid":"JM21iBwN7_VeX8iUbMa5Yg","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"• Forma: Generalmente circular, sin intrones, proteínas tipo histonas ausentes.","guid":"Fp1pFlb0kfc32mJ3MWjbPw","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"• Replicación: Unión al mesosoma (membrana citoplasmática).","guid":"ca_c7l5DaNlh_Qw8EJSTIQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"105","text":"• Plásmidos:","guid":"BVlDVCcVBRNeOf0gAbjOKw","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"• Definición: ADN extracromosómico, menor tamaño, puede portar genes de resistencia o virulencia.","guid":"JqyKwiO_7-NjPZrFF2R8sw","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"109","text":"• Ejemplo: E. coli (plásmido con genes de diarrea en viajeros e infantes).","guid":"FCvj8VzzKCcQ79Z7C4XaIw","children":[]}]},{"id":"112","parent":"105","text":"Ribosomas:","guid":"Mic_yxu2vZF-VuPyB50cXw","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"• Composición: Riboproteínas formadas por RNA ribosomal y proteínas.","guid":"EJsglx64dXYJYQzMbLuDTg","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"• Función: Síntesis de proteínas.","guid":"SL_LEgQMEXkr2hPybY2Amg","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"112","text":"• Diferencias con eucariotas: Menor tamaño, organización diferente.","guid":"IBoBbgo53IZaVDn8NrdqhA","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"112","text":"• Importancia Clínica: Objetivo para antibióticos que inhiben la síntesis proteica bacteriana (toxicidad selectiva).","guid":"YS5ufRIunHRoIEXDUt5Law","children":[]}]},{"id":"117","parent":"105","text":"• Cromosoma Bacteriano:","guid":"XuuqeQ5_lnI1C32eJ6t1iw","children":[{"id":"118","parent":"117","text":"• Forma: Generalmente circular, doble hebra.","guid":"cTJXEkGs2613hBbNF97h1A","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"117","text":"• Tamaño: ~4x10⁶ pares de bases (pb), 4000 genes.","guid":"ZWzLkVrBsZIvQ16IeZivgg","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"117","text":"• Organización: Ocupa ~10% del volumen celular.","guid":"N7TZuUAzNQMFHommSE_6UA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"121","parent":"0","text":"Mecanismos de\\NTransferencia de DNA:","guid":"Wy8gnEer_sku8ubtNAQowQ","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"Transformación:","guid":"AbvMllF9WaIfLCf_ci3R4w","children":[{"id":"123","parent":"122","text":"• Definición: Captura de DNA desnudo desde el medio ambiente.","guid":"Eoun62DlkZAVOPYmMqWpWg","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"122","text":"• Proceso: DNA exógeno es incorporado por bacterias competentes.","guid":"ax9uFm-NMCJpXRPeTE3ckw","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"122","text":"• Ejemplo: Experimento de Griffith (1928) con Streptococcus pneumoniae.","guid":"G5qroQKfBoxn-RqFDM0CtA","children":[]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"121","text":"Conjugación:","guid":"REviOV99MVIkq-SIKbityg","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"• Definición: Transferencia de material genético de una bacteria donadora (F⁺) a una receptora (F⁻) a través de un pilus.","guid":"Oj7i5FPvQxAjUV1NcfO8nQ","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"126","text":"• Plásmido F: Codifica los genes necesarios para la conjugación; factor de fertilidad.","guid":"FCJ4Eyhv5vM6Q7btcw4ijA","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"126","text":"• Proceso:","guid":"KW0_UXtid19fYuqAbbkhig","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"• Formación de un puente de conjugación.","guid":"Nu99ZW9PNIsauZgYSXslUA","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"• Transferencia de un segmento de DNA del plásmido F.","guid":"UDTGHC_yjj58IM6qO1Q0Mg","children":[]}]},{"id":"132","parent":"126","text":"• Variantes:","guid":"Wt-osQQOzwkXcc9VFR6LlQ","children":[{"id":"133","parent":"132","text":"• Hfr (High Frequency Recombination): Plásmido F integrado en el cromosoma, transfiriendo genes cromosómicos.","guid":"H3--YGV94okHohDGITuK9w","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"132","text":"• F’ (F-prima): Plásmido que contiene genes cromosómicos tras escisión.","guid":"Nvs8KybOOMUTaVzaUpXnzA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"135","parent":"121","text":"Transducción:","guid":"V_4SGTrDLKIHEkgybCCKLQ","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"• Definición: Transferencia de DNA bacteriano mediante un bacteriófago (virus de bacterias).","guid":"YzMTlUFV_x9fLqy5GiKQ-g","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"135","text":"• Tipos:","guid":"eWHwoS4wdfYBxNhgVEGZUg","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"• Generalizada: Cualquier gen bacteriano puede ser transferido.","guid":"MKUzq3noRNFjnbZKANn5xw","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"• Especializada: Solo genes específicos son transferidos.","guid":"KdrTD1--hPU8Li35SVqRcA","children":[]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"135","text":"• Ejemplos:","guid":"Mj9E_xk2p7VpYCToCj1XGA","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"• Fagos P1 y λ en E. coli.","guid":"RTxnfkPQPr9qlhxnfDejqQ","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"• Fago P22 en Salmonella Typhimurium.","guid":"ap53hH3_eUFOzYt1FAu21Q","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"0","text":"Elementos\\NGenéticos Móviles:","guid":"FVTMu20oLXhqcsG1LxOsmw","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"Transposones:","guid":"FKu0JR91x6VCqjdQWegbow","children":[{"id":"145","parent":"144","text":"• Definición: Elementos genéticos móviles que pueden transponer de un lugar a otro en el genoma, o entre plásmidos y cromosomas.","guid":"U_nUV3BybRp2XeFFNyzn7A","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"144","text":"• Función: Codifican para transposasas (enzimas que permiten la transposición).","guid":"MchsOlWMjf9RT3jmYm2f5Q","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"144","text":"• Importancia Clínica: Pueden portar genes de resistencia a antibióticos, lo que facilita su diseminación entre bacterias.","guid":"T3TS0DTtLzBjR5mseU-l4A","children":[]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"143","text":"Mutaciones:","guid":"Y0YGZS1AU7dWH79MTeR96Q","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"1. Definición:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"• Cambio heredable en la secuencia de DNA.","guid":"fOu01GJDe9QPmlzPUOWJKw","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"• Tipos:","guid":"UrXo7gX4PhUIEnEXBH5VKA","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"• Espontáneas: Ocurren durante la replicación del DNA.","guid":"W4TMFFlh6f1m6_UNKvme5A","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"• Inducidas: Provocadas por mutágenos (químicos, radiación, transposones).","guid":"Dk8ZLUozjrkkSUTEIvrNUw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"148","text":"2. Tipos de Mutaciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"• Puntuales: Cambio de una base por otra (transición/transversión), inserción o deleción.","guid":"aalWX2bzfBR84uj2TO9cxA","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"154","text":"• Mutaciones sin sentido: Crean un codón de terminación prematuro.","guid":"FDPPy1MCqEMa09qtP3OcxA","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"154","text":"• Mutaciones de sentido equivocado: Codifican para un aminoácido diferente.","guid":"d-_zBXzED2xkFVpdSw2zvQ","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"154","text":"• Mutaciones por corrimiento del marco de lectura: Inserciones o deleciones que alteran el marco de lectura, afectando la síntesis proteica.","guid":"YHkci1z4sUlQarl0XWTRXw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"0","text":"Bacterias\\NPatógenas:","guid":"cOIk4z1VPUkq2WiNK_1sOw","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"Definición:","guid":"d7iAKj3rhRV-KKIeC-xP9Q","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"• Microorganismos que causan enfermedad en el hospedero.","guid":"PzwtHWAFFkMuSlqKEfIWDA","children":[]}]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"• Tipos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"• Patógenos específicos: Producen enfermedades bien definidas (e.g., Neisseria gonorrhoeae).","guid":"Zf1UWDZcy6EWcGs0QYIgbA","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"162","text":"• Oportunistas: Generalmente no patógenos, pero pueden causar enfermedades en ciertas condiciones (e. g., especies del género Bacteroides).","guid":"D761nn1cYEJse79RHg3OzA","children":[]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"159","text":"• Mecanismos de\\NPatogenicidad:","guid":"R4_u-xDFBBVBCJwfMTlFWg","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"• Adherencia e invasión del hospedero.","guid":"EO4tWBj8fMxLX-y5CN4gXQ","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"• Producción de toxinas.","guid":"FcCMOC91RxdT69QadjmoxA","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"165","text":"• Resistencia a la respuesta inmune del hospedero.","guid":"DG34YCRWjY5TnnojS6olfg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"169","parent":"0","text":"Entrada del Patógeno y\\NColonización Inicial:","guid":"Kz_M-CTtSsJh8DS_JKG9mQ","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"• Rutas de Entrada:","guid":"BFuj0gHo1K5dnDuKalj4Kg","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"• Membranas mucosas: Respiratorias, gastrointestinales, genitourinarias, conjuntivas.","guid":"OEWgT3QMpr4r2xiXSARV7g","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"• Piel: A través de lesiones, folículos pilosos, o conductos glandulares.","guid":"cWkHABhW1-hmEiS6OPj1_A","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"• Otras vías: Parenteral, transfusiones, transplacentaria.","guid":"KRvb_ScawNlqMjtWINRcJw","children":[]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"169","text":"• Ejemplos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"• Streptococcus pneumoniae causa neumonía cuando se inhala, pero no al ser ingerido.","guid":"ZQZF7mha3XUswKwddfRzRw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"0","text":"Adherencia\\NBacteriana:","guid":"D-ZeUVz-aStPtFffPqmElg","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"• Mediada por adhesinas: Moléculas en la superficie bacteriana que se unen a receptores en las células del hospedero.","guid":"AVdaQXggmNZ-0pOkFxfmeQ","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"• Factores de\\NVirulencia:","guid":"TkX13CCsZgtLSnMVT51QHQ","children":[{"id":"179","parent":"178","text":"• Cápsula externa en E. coli (EPEC).","guid":"J5Xf7VK-Z78NUY89NAPYTg","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"178","text":"• Fimbrias codificadas por plásmidos en E. coli (ETEC).","guid":"dxT1TWDwCWF_rf3Me3CZHw","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"178","text":"• Fimbrias de Neisseria gonorrhoeae para adherencia al epitelio urogenital.","guid":"YtjeD11KOVZlyZFKGx5-Xg","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"178","text":"• Fimbrias de Haemophilus influenzae tipo b para invasión.","guid":"UVbgFBGkqeFjItRMQr_nFQ","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"178","text":"• Fimbrias en enterobacterias (Salmonella, E. coli) para unión a manosa en glicoproteínas.","guid":"KfuByUk0-QZ7uN0RUxddxg","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"178","text":"• Proteína F de Streptococcus pyogenes para adherencia a fibronectina.","guid":"cE-532XrGGdz67nuVVX_zg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"185","parent":"0","text":"Invasividad:","guid":"QfbUkzdenrxDYZAhJo_IGQ","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"• Necesidad de Invadir:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"• La mayoría de las bacterias patógenas invaden células del hospedero para causar enfermedad.","guid":"GMz-4UodBrlmtTaXQGLezw","children":[]}]},{"id":"188","parent":"185","text":"• Adhesión y Señalización:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"189","parent":"188","text":"• Adherencia a células del hospedero estimula la invasión.","guid":"HNtueHQGxdR0ZrcdE_Bjxg","children":[]}]},{"id":"190","parent":"185","text":"• Proteínas Invasinas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"• Facilitan la penetración del patógeno en células del hospedero.","guid":"VPbPNXQUtOkPYPzlN8-tRA","children":[]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"185","text":"• Evasión de la Respuesta Inmune:","guid":"UV7uP3Uqji9S7iujIrXOUw","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"• Shigella, Listeria, Yersinia, y Salmonella invaden células epiteliales y no fagocíticas.","guid":"Bs84EDYQ_-9ldbVoMMq52Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"194","parent":"185","text":"• Estrategias de Supervivencia\\NIntracelular:","guid":"f0X49mEuknkD4hegb5Wy1Q","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"• Modificación del citoesqueleto.","guid":"Rxmq4XfN0Y5E67KjFV-gvQ","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"194","text":"• Supervivencia dentro de vacuolas.","guid":"GHo3mRA2Jbhk_PDbMUc2eg","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"194","text":"• Evasión de mecanismos destructivos del hospedero.","guid":"WlMsckuyJ3JxqhVJdy6a6g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"0","text":"Toxinas\\NBacterianas:","guid":"KdCo_EtR5bZ1aOmpW_foxw","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"1. Exotoxinas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"200","parent":"199","text":"• Definición: Toxinas secretadas por bacterias que actúan sobre tejidos específicos del hospedero.","guid":"P7jtRmYQzGYLHv6wFK-8fA","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"199","text":"• Clasificación:","guid":"VX6VUzOv80pHRHuvVMSOSQ","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"• Neurotoxinas: Afectan el sistema nervioso.","guid":"WiWBTxp_-5ZMf2nAK4Rvjg","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"201","text":"• Enterotoxinas: Afectan el sistema digestivo.","guid":"D6qJxR9tlWNOOj3iFnnB1g","children":[]}]},{"id":"204","parent":"199","text":"• Características:","guid":"QvRk3QlF88JxV9FiW26cdg","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"• Son proteínas, generalmente termolábiles.","guid":"FN6FxEsmk09EWkEeW_gwpQ","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"204","text":"• Pueden ser inactivadas para producir toxoides utilizados en vacunas (e.g., toxoide tetánico).","guid":"GXwZelZUwj0MtdLxc89F7A","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"204","text":"• Ejemplos: Bacillus, Clostridium, Staphylococcus, Streptococcus, Vibrio.","guid":"Igbpr35f6Dpq_eDXYb_W9g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"208","parent":"198","text":"2. Endotoxinas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"209","parent":"208","text":"• Definición: Compuestas por lipopolisacáridos (LPS) en la membrana externa de bacterias Gram-negativas.","guid":"ZHC0oXYc34d2b5NyPpY18A","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"208","text":"• Acción: Liberadas tras la destrucción de la bacteria; provocan respuestas inmunitarias intensas.","guid":"EJzbHULu_TJqGqV_IEdk4w","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"208","text":"• Toxicidad: Generalmente más débil que la de las exotoxinas, pero pueden causar shock y muerte en infecciones graves.","guid":"YlySljhU42E2wSa5N9sn6Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"212","parent":"198","text":"3. Enzimas Extracelulares:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"• Función: Degradan componentes del tejido del hospedero facilitando la diseminación del patógeno.","guid":"bATWq34FomgMn7YyAONcbw","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"212","text":"• Ejemplos:","guid":"SSw1uFD591Bc240UDCCalQ","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"• Hialuronidasa: Degrada el ácido hialurónico en tejido conectivo.","guid":"Wj_rEk4zXndnjzcMc7wEjQ","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"214","text":"• Colagenasa: Degrada colágeno; producida por Clostridium histolyticum.","guid":"JIggtHRFCf1ni0p5Ro8KZA","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"214","text":"• Neuraminidasa: Degrada ácido neuramínico; producida por Vibrio cholerae.","guid":"cqTyN1KJK1AoTuFaVxWm2A","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"214","text":"• Estreptoquinasa y Estafiloquinasa: Convertir plasminógeno en plasmina, facilitando la diseminación.","guid":"SKYK2B6-dMwVq9zJWULl9Q","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"0","text":"Mecanismos de\\NResistencia a Infecciones:","guid":"ZwijSHO_zZtjlQUnQjfD5A","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"1. Resistencia No\\NEspecífica:","guid":"YY8_aWN4kMIpLL5gKjVKQQ","children":[{"id":"221","parent":"220","text":"• Función: Protección contra cualquier patógeno, independiente de la especie.","guid":"Ya1x_n_Ggkh5ikrYRAoElA","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"220","text":"• Componentes:","guid":"X3IlUA8GFBk7Ka9oUhcXiA","children":[{"id":"223","parent":"222","text":"• Barreras físicas: Piel, membranas mucosas.","guid":"OBtlqTBLcZF75Sx9JCA8VA","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"222","text":"• Defensas químicas: Lisozima en fluidos corporales, pH ácido.","guid":"LlET-giE4q8lA5jEd31Jsg","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"222","text":"• Defensas celulares: Fagocitosis por macrófagos y neutrófilos.","guid":"WX7aAAHfJdgDneRHM77FEg","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"222","text":"• Inflamación: Respuesta inflamatoria que incluye la activación de células inmunes y liberación de mediadores.","guid":"UBKET2stG1MnesmfdJqlBA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"227","parent":"219","text":"2. Resistencia\\NEspecífica:","guid":"LU3soSPTqJ4a2r9vW58Amw","children":[{"id":"228","parent":"227","text":"• Función: Defensa inducida por un patógeno específico.","guid":"AjcFjj7YmykDeDA3Y-R3jA","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"227","text":"• Características: Involucra la respuesta inmune adaptativa, incluyendo la producción de anticuerpos específicos y la activación de células T para atacar patógenos específicos.","guid":"Pp8dcX0Cew8n7nwhdrqDGg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"230","parent":"0","text":"Mecanismos Bacterianos de Evasión de las\\NDefensas del Cuerpo Humano:","guid":"O2vMZBKH7BR2O-ylWKdwmw","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"1. Resistencia Inespecífica:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"232","parent":"231","text":"• Cápsula: Protege contra la fagocitosis (e.g., Bacillus anthracis).","guid":"LFiLTj_eWDNTHEpNBddlTg","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"231","text":"• LPS y otras barreras: Protección contra la lisis mediada por complementos o lisozima.","guid":"Qb1-C1a6LpQ5lipgEdACWw","children":[]}]},{"id":"234","parent":"230","text":"2. Destrucción de Fagocitos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"235","parent":"234","text":"• Mecanismo: Lisis de fagocitos mediada por toxinas, e.g., Staphylococcus y Streptococcus.","guid":"QedJ6GEQ9AAGaqdfIVlvOA","children":[]}]},{"id":"236","parent":"230","text":"3. Evasión de la\\NRespuesta Inmune:","guid":"cBcIGUGUVsdzcIbAUaZHgg","children":[{"id":"237","parent":"236","text":"• Estrategias:","guid":"JQzniRydRSF725HEJ0PtFw","children":[{"id":"238","parent":"237","text":"• Tolerancia inmunológica.","guid":"W3XgSn9TwfsLKGSjGhT9vA","children":[]},{"id":"239","parent":"237","text":"• Inmunosupresión.","guid":"fFY9CjMW4MQQz4DWKaQpqw","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"237","text":"• Persistencia del patógeno.","guid":"VuqJYyuqQEUFQypGA0MUsQ","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"237","text":"• Variación antigénica (e.g., Borrelia en fiebre recurrente).","guid":"a4iYeFhfdJMJGnn_LUYWhA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"242","parent":"0","text":"Reservorios de Bacterias\\NPatógenas para el Hombre:","guid":"Ux3AuGO1DR9441bsBV0Ftw","children":[{"id":"243","parent":"242","text":"1. Reservorio\\NHumano:","guid":"cdJPZhbALcpvOCZXeOdmaw","children":[{"id":"244","parent":"243","text":"• Principal fuente de enfermedades infecciosas (e.g., fiebre tifoidea, infecciones venéreas).","guid":"LxmjKEKwpF8_FhjfcQDtEA","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"243","text":"• Papel importante en la propagación de patógenos.","guid":"I8GYX0WAwD4SWlxIE9igeA","children":[]}]},{"id":"246","parent":"242","text":"2. Reservorio\\NAnimal:","guid":"N53tfyxRjygEZdGCW1-F3w","children":[{"id":"247","parent":"246","text":"• Zoonosis: Enfermedades transmitidas desde animales (e.g., carbunco bacteriano, brucelosis, salmonelosis).","guid":"BxUXBQXK4wllfuf7LCH-jg","children":[]},{"id":"248","parent":"246","text":"• Ejemplos: Ganado, tortugas, garrapatas.","guid":"ImgoKmFaeb9TZeulfd4IdA","children":[]}]},{"id":"249","parent":"242","text":"3. Reservorio\\NNo Viviente:","guid":"ZEtBSnTtSSBtO3ZJE2Tkcg","children":[{"id":"250","parent":"249","text":"• Ambiente: Suelo, agua, o alimentos contaminados.","guid":"YK47ul6OUEgX8wYwXQR4xA","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"249","text":"• Patógenos: Clostridium spp. (botulismo, tétano).","guid":"EaUxDSjChwcGqKJwaI-6cA","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"249","text":"• Importancia: Fuente de infecciones gastrointestinales por alimentos o agua contaminados.","guid":"VGzHTAvrzLZr0s8hP_VfxQ","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":252,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Infectología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Infectología","filename":"Micro. - Generalidades de las bacterias-2024","id":"map_1160","resolved_references":[]}